keywords proposition propositions
---

@@YPropositions@@N are personal postman-issued tasks that can be completed for
rewards. You can hold up to @@Y3@@N propositions at once.

@@WCommands@@N
  proposition request
    Ask a postman for a random dynamic proposition and place it in a free slot.

  proposition list
    While with a postman, view all available static propositions and
    their pseudo-level range requirements.

  proposition accept <number>
    While with a postman, accept the numbered static proposition from
    @@Yproposition list@@N into a free slot (only offered by that specific
    postmaster).

  proposition status
    View progress for every active proposition slot.

  proposition complete
    While with a postman, turn in one completed proposition for rewards.

  proposition cancel <slot#>
    Cancel the proposition in the given slot (1-3).

@@WProposition types@@N
  1) Kill Variety
     Defeat several distinct target mobs.

  2) Collect Items
     Obtain listed items (credit is granted when they enter inventory).

  3) Kill Count
     Defeat a specific number of one target mob type.

@@WStatic proposition behavior@@N
- Static propositions are predefined templates offered by postmen.
- Each static proposition is tied to a specific postmaster NPC vnum.
- Each static proposition has minimum and maximum pseudo-level requirements.
- After a static proposition is completed and turned in, it is marked complete
  for that character.
- Completed static propositions no longer appear in @@Yproposition list@@N and
  cannot be accepted again.

@@WRewards@@N
- Dynamic propositions reward gold and quest points based on pseudo level.
- Static propositions can define fixed gold/quest-point rewards.
- Static propositions may also grant item rewards on completion.

@@WNotes@@N
- You must be with a postman for @@Yrequest@@N, @@Ylist@@N, @@Yaccept@@N, and @@Ycomplete@@N.
- @@Ystatus@@N and @@Ycancel@@N can be used anywhere.
- Cancelling a @@Ydynamic@@N proposition adds a 15 minute cooldown before
  you can request another dynamic proposition.
- Static propositions can still be accepted during this cooldown.
